%description:

Tests that the client restarts the 'secs' clock when a renewal begins
(RFC 2131 §3.1: 'secs' counts from the start of the address acquisition *or
renewal* process). The client first completes DORA and binds the lease, then
at T1 (renewalTime) it enters RENEWING and sends a unicast DHCPREQUEST. With
the fix, dhcpStartTime is reset as the renewal starts, so that request carries
secs = 0; before the fix it would have carried secs ~= renewalTime, because
the clock was still counting from the original DORA.

The lease time is 3600s, so T1 fires at ~1800s. The RENEWING request is the only
DHCPREQUEST sent with broadcast = false (REQUESTING/REBINDING use broadcast),
which lets us pin the assertion to the renewal specifically. Applications log
at DETAIL level so the DhcpMessage field dump is visible.

%inifile: omnetpp.ini

[General]
network = Test
ned-path = .;../../../../src;../../lib
cmdenv-express-mode = false
cmdenv-log-prefix = "[%t %M] "
sim-time-limit = 2400s

**.app[*].cmdenv-log-level = detail
**.status.cmdenv-log-level = detail
**.cmdenv-log-level = off

*.configurator.config = xml("<config><interface hosts='server' address='192.168.1.1' netmask='255.255.255.0'/></config>")

*.server.numApps = 1
*.server.app[0].typename = "DhcpServer"
*.server.app[0].numReservedAddresses = 100
*.server.app[0].maxNumClients = 10
*.server.app[0].gateway = "192.168.1.1"
*.server.app[0].leaseTime = 3600s

*.client.numApps = 1
*.client.app[0].typename = "DhcpClient"

%file: test.ned

import inet.test.moduletest.lib.*;
import inet.node.ethernet.Eth10M;
import inet.node.ethernet.EthernetSwitch;
import inet.node.inet.StandardHost;
import inet.networklayer.configurator.ipv4.Ipv4NetworkConfigurator;

network Test
{
    submodules:
        configurator: Ipv4NetworkConfigurator;
        switch: EthernetSwitch;
        server: StandardHost;
        client: StandardHost;
    connections:
        server.ethg++ <--> Eth10M <--> switch.ethg++;
        client.ethg++ <--> Eth10M <--> switch.ethg++;
}

%# Strip ANSI styling emitted by the EV_FIELD packet dump.
%subst: /\x1B\[[0-9;]*m//

%# The client must actually reach the RENEWING state (T1 fired).
%# The unicast renewal DHCPREQUEST must carry secs = 0: the clock was reset as
%# the renewal began, not left counting from the original DORA (~10s ago).
%contains-regex: stdout
\[1800\.[0-9]+ Test.client.app\[0\]\] T1 expired\. Starting RENEWING state\.
\[1800\.[0-9]+ Test.client.app\[0\]\] Sending DHCPREQUEST extending lease for IP 192\.168\.1\.100 via unicast to 192\.168\.1\.1\.
\[1800\.[0-9]+ Test.client.app\[0\]\] Sending DHCP message, msg = \(Packet\)DHCPREQUEST .*secs = 0, broadcast = false

%# Regression guard: no unicast (renewal) DHCPREQUEST may carry a positive secs;
%# that would mean the clock kept running from acquisition instead of resetting.
%not-contains-regex: stdout
Sending DHCP message, msg = \(Packet\)DHCPREQUEST .*secs = [1-9][0-9]*, broadcast = false

%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
